data.description: Privacy, acreage and horse farm potential are just a few of the attributes of this fantastic property. As you travel along the tree lined driveway you will see several acres of property suitable for a pasture with an existing barn. You must keep going in order to get a glimpse of the beautiful Cape Cod style home that is privately nestled among the trees. The home offers solid oak floors, vaulted ceilings and lots of natural light. There are two primary bedrooms on the main level with their own walk in closets and bathrooms (one of which is ADA friendly) as well as two more rooms and a bathroom located on the front hall. If that is not enough room, there is a bonus room for guests or hang out area. The kitchen is a chef's dream with high end appliances such as the six burner Wolf cooktop and Fisher & Paykel wall oven. Imagine cozying up to the gas assist fireplace or hanging out on the beautiful porches at the end of a day to relax. Located only 12 minutes away from the TIEC.
